60 Druid<br>
Vexare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333399>(7/26/02 3:29:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bleh</span><hr size=1> While the nerf does remove an overpowered item it also breaks gameplay in 2 ways.<br>
<br>
<br>
PROBLEM <br>
<br>
First it makes possible a very simple strategy that can be used to prevent anyone from dispelling you.<br>
<br>
Simply keep insta buffs at the top of your stack (2 to prevent pumice, 3 if you expect to prevent a caster from annulling you) and refresh them every time they get dispelled.<br>
<br>
DESCRIPTION<br>
<br>
The problem with the effectiveness of this strategy is that in some cases it basicly grants you an automatic win with no counter  As when you are flying over the head of a melee who can't remove your lev or when you have a duel wielding melee killing himself on a ds he can't remove.<br>
<br>
Previously wands and egg shaped pumice served to get around this.<br>
<br>
SOLUTION<br>
<br>
Tag all insta spells as non removable so that cancel, nullify, and annul magic will skip right over them.  Smart pvpers will still be able to bury buffs but they can't simply deny their oponents the ability to debuff them at all.<br>
<br>
PROBLEM<br>
<br>
Second it makes it impossible for pure melee to use dispelling items while being hit by a pet.  <br>
<br>
DESCRIPTION<br>
<br>
The problem with this lies not only with the fact that the melee can't dispell his oponents buffs but more so with the fact that the melee can't dispell negative spells like unresistable dots.<br>
<br>
SOLUTION<br>
<br>
Give melees a low lvl of channeling skill so they will be able to remove dots/negative effects while being hit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzoffo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zoffo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333399>(8/5/02 2:12:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bleh</span><hr size=1> OMG...I won't even comment on the last poster.  If you think casters have any net advantage over melee's...well I guess you do not pvp much.<br>
<br>
Ode to unbalance -<br>
<br>
A druid running followed by a ranger,<br>
the ranger's bow loosing on the run,<br>
if the druid stops to cast,<br>
ranger lands the blows,<br>
if the druid keeps running,<br>
his arse gets full of arrows.<br>
<br>
I will be glad if they nerf these items. <p>Nillipus + Taxidermy = hours of fun.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzoffo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zoffo</A> at: 8/27/02 4:25:24 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uelethiomeltimberfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ElethiomelTimberfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Just got my shots!</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#333399>(8/14/02 6:37:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> yep</span><hr size=1> not to mention the fact that pumices are usually used on YOURSELF, not other casters.<br>
<br>
In PvP, people usually pumice off dots, snare, etc. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utsalarianthewanderer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tsalarian the Wanderer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#333399>(8/29/02 4:24:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: yep</span><hr size=1> Why would you want to run away from a ranger? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8678" target="_blank">
