<BR>Hierophant of Tunare
<BR>Antonius Bayle </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzoffo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zoffo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#333399>(8/29/02 8:22:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: yep</span><hr size=1> Why would I run from a ranger - <br>
<br>
Well, I was in a zone skilling my defense...the first ranger that attacked me fled when he was at 1 bub hp, and since I was on a mission to max def, I let him go.<br>
<br>
Not much longer another ranger attacked me.  I had just finished a mob (remember, I am skilling def here) so I was about 2 bub hp...he takes a swipe at me and does 89 dmg.  I run so I can get a heal off...and he is sniping me with arrows which are landing for 35ish.  Anyway, I used the distance gained when he tried to cast a snare to get a heal off and was good hp-wise.<br>
<br>
So next I am thinking what I can do about this ranger that hits for 89 (I am level 34 at the time, and 89 dmg is a lot...even if your 60) and his arrows are landing (while he is running) for 35ish.  Quite a dilemma if you ask me.<br>
<br>
Now the mystery...I had greater wolf form on, and I could not out run him.  No matter what I did (even just running completely straight, not touching left or right keys) he did not lose ground at all.  So where did he get a sow fast enough to keep up with my gwf?  Immy buffed by another player somewhere in zone?  That was my guess.<br>
<br>
I did not attempt a snare since I could not get distance, and it surely would have been futile anyway as a ranger twink hitting for 90 and shooting for 35 is NOT going to have low enough MR for me to land a snare.<br>
<br>
I could not get enough distance to cast any useful spell in my arsenal...not even cancel magic.<br>
<br>
So, what does a druid do in this situation?  Please enlighten me...I am a fair to good pvp'er, I am not uber twinked (bought every item on me for 200pp or less...most items 100 or less, save for shroud of nature which I traded a 500pp item for)...heck, I don't even consider myself mini-twinked...heh.<br>
<br>
I am learning slowly but surely how to deal with each class and have won all of my pvp encounters thus far that have not resulted in a draw (I am sure I will die tonight after saying this...heheh.)<br>
<br>
How does a druid deal with a ranger that hits/shoots for 90/35 and has equal speed and was quite a good follower (I was juking the best I could using hills, trees, anything I could find...and he stayed with me...he did really well at that IMO).<br>
<br>
I was stumped...so I just ran.  I could have hill bug'd him, but that is ghey IMO, I like fair fights (i.e. no cheating...I do not have a problem with having the upper hand though...all is fair in war, save for cheating...heh.)<br>
<br>
Any suggestions on this special case are welcome.  I really don't have the money for any insta click or even regular click dispell items.  Are there any insta click dispell items for decent prices (or not requiring a raid sized element to obtain) ???<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
Zoffo Moffo <p><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/zoffo/fullsize/zsdark.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoakendalefw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oakendale FW</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#333399>(8/29/02 10:30:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmmm</span><hr size=1> Rangers with am3 and ts &gt; druids unless you got some nifftah landscape to hide around in..... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Oakendale ForestWalker<br>
60 Druid<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utsalarianthewanderer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tsalarian the Wanderer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333399>(8/30/02 5:06:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> Well, I can only speak how I myself handle rangers...<br>
I hug em... of course you have a problem if you get jumped etc. Hug em and use DS especially, and dots. When close, they won't be able to use their insane ranged dmg with AM3,EQ with dmg16 arrow etc (imo this part about rangers is equally bugged as the wall/arroww bug).<br>
60 Ranger with Primal Bow or better, AM3,EQ dmg16, TS, crit + standing still hurts like hell.<br>
<br>
I also use fast nukes, so he won't get too far away and get too many arrows off till I reach him again (sunder + scoriae works fine for me). A ranger melee'ing me would loose hps at the same rate or faster than me. I'd much rather take that than arrows. If ranger decides that he wants to melee me, I'd just heal with chloroblast... usually channels through, and he'd be gone easy (and fast, especially if he's hasted, hehe). Usually, they don't want to hit me once they realize the DS tho.<br>
<br>
Only problem I see is him using golem wands on me, which sucks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I don't play on a PvP server, so I don't have the same point of view on PvP as you have. When I face an opponent, I'm usually ready for it. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8678" target="_blank">
Elder Tsalarian the Wanderer</a>
<BR>Hierophant of Tunare
<BR>Antonius Bayle </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzoffo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zoffo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#333399>(8/30/02 11:41:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> Interesting...hug them eh.  That just might have worked if I had a decent ds up...which I did not because I was trying go keep my def skilling mobs alive as long as possible.  In addition, I could not get distance to open book and get ds in spell slot, let alone cast.<br>
<br>
I think that special situation is just one of those where the druid has to get away.  IMO, the worst possible melee class can own a great melee class (player skills being equal) if one is caught geared/buffed/spell gem'd up for PVE and not PVP.<br>
<br>
It was fun, and I was glad that he was not able to kill me.  I love how druids can survive in so many poor situations. <p><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/zoffo/fullsize/zsdark.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showPrevMessage?topicID=52.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showNextMessage?topicID=52.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=9><img src=http://dev.thedruidsgrove.org/images/forum/addreplya.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.emailToFriend?topicID=52.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.threadControl?topicID=52.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=52.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=52.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option v